FBIS4-44095 "drweu123_i_94007" FBIS-WEU-94-123 Daily Report 24 Jun 1994 FRANCE Government Officials, Others Comment on Rwanda Government Officials, Others Comment on Rwanda Berlusconi Supports Sending Troops LD2406202594 Paris France-2 Television Network in French 1830 GMT 24 Jun 94 LD2406202594 Paris France-2 Television Network French BFN [Excerpts] Six European countries -- Belgium, the Netherlands, Portugual, Spain, Germany, and the United Kingdom -- today expressed their readiness to offer logistical or humanitarian support for Operation Turquoise. For its part, Italy is ready to send soldiers, but only under certain conditions. More details from Arlette Chabot, our special envoy to the European summit in Corfu: [Chabot] [passage omitted] Italy alone is ready to send soldiers, as many as 5,000, if Mr. Berlusconi can persuade his cabinet. [Begin Berlusconi recording] I have just spoken with my defense minister. We are organizing everything, and I believe we will succeed in persuading those concerned. [Chabot] Does this mean that you will send soldiers? [Berlusconi] Soldiers with a field hospital. [Chabot] In Rwanda? With French soldiers? [Berlusconi] I do not know; if we can, I hope we can coordinate. [end recording] [passage omitted]
